content:
N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 9 ยง 2.7 - Executive Order No. 7: Relating to extended unemployment insurance benefits

State Regulations
I, Malcolm Wilson, Governor of the State of New York, by
virtue of the authority vested in me by subdivision 6 of section
601
of the Labor Law
do hereby prolong through July 7, 1974 the period during which the
applicability of the provisions of item (ii) of subparagraph (1) of paragraph
(b) of subdivision 1 of section
601
of the Labor Law, and of the reference to such item in subparagraph (2) of such paragraph, is
suspended, as originally specified in Executive Order Number 3 of February 1, 1974, and as prolonged by Executive Order Number 6 of March 29, 1974. Signed: Malcolm A. Wilson

Dated: July 1, 1974
